displayList

public static java.lang.String displayList(java.lang.String[] asItems)
Converts an array of items into a textual list depending on the number of items:
  1. a
  2. a and b
  3. a, b and c
  4. a, b, c and d
I believe this list now matches OU house style in omitting the comma before 'and'.

Parameters:
asItems - List of any number of string items (0..)
Returns:
String representing those items

sqlQuote

public static java.lang.String sqlQuote(java.lang.String s)
Quotes a string for SQL - doubles any inner quotes and add the two surrounding quotes. Use this for *any* quote in SQL, even if sure the string doesn't have ' inside (just to be on the safe side). There should be no ' character literals in SQL queries/update strings in this code.

Parameters:
s - Input string
Returns:
String surrounded by single quotes and escaped as necessary
